# Percentage Order Book

## Overview

This is a Next.js-based web application that provides real-time information about cryptocurrency markets. It allows users to view market data, buy and sell orders, and recent transactions for various cryptocurrency pairs. The application features a responsive design, dark/light theme support, and uses Decimal.js for precise financial calculations.

## Features

- Real-time cryptocurrency market data
- Buy and sell order books
- Recent transactions list
- Percentage-based order calculations
- Dark and light theme support
- 1 Finger swipe gesture support for mobile devices
- Responsive design for desktop and mobile devices
- Client-side pagination for market listings

## Technologies Used

- [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) - React framework for server-side rendering and static site generation
- [React](https://reactjs.org/) - JavaScript library for building user interfaces
- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) - Typed superset of JavaScript
- [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) - Utility-first CSS framework
- [Decimal.js](https://mikemcl.github.io/decimal.js/) - Arbitrary-precision decimal library
- [next-themes](https://github.com/pacocoursey/next-themes) - Theme management for Next.js
- [Lucide React](https://lucide.dev/) - Icon set for React

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (version 20 or later)
- npm (comes with Node.js) or yarn

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/percentage-based-order-book.git
   ```
2. Navigate to the project directory:
   ```bash
   yarn install
   ```
   ```bash
   yarn dev
   ```
3. Open your browser and visit http://localhost:3000 to access the application.
